TRAIL – Taiwan Responsible AI License
Version 0.1, September 30, 2025

Preamble
TRAIL combines LGPL copyleft (modifications must be open, linking exception allowed) with RAIL responsible use (prohibited harmful uses).
This license applies to three components:
TRAIL-M: Models & Weights
TRAIL-S: Source Code & Complementary Material
TRAIL-D: Datasets

Definitions
(a) Model: Machine learning architecture, weights, parameters (incl. optimizer states).
(b) Complementary Material: Code, scripts, docs used to define, train, evaluate, and run models.
(c) Dataset: Data used for training or evaluation.
(d) Derivative Work: Any modification, retraining, distillation, conversion, or adaptation of the Licensed Work.
(e) Linked Work: Applications that only call or load the model/library without modification.
(f) Distribution: Making the Licensed Work available (download, API, remote access, etc.).
(g) Output: The results produced by the model.
(h) "You" (or "Your") means an individual or legal entity exercising permissions granted by this License and/or making use of the Model for whichever purpose and in any field of use, including usage of the Model in an end-use application - e.g. chatbot, translator, image generator.

Section I: Intellectual Property Rights

Copyright
Worldwide, free, irrevocable rights to use, modify, distribute the Licensed Work and Derivatives.

Patent
Patent rights necessary to use the Licensed Work are granted. If you sue the Licensor, this license terminates.

Section II: TRAIL-M (Models & Weights)

Copyleft Requirement
If you modify or create derivative models and distribute them, you must release them under TRAIL-M, with accessible weights or code.

Linking Exception
If you only call the model (API, inference, load unmodified weights), your application may use any license and need not be open-sourced.

Distribution Conditions
Distributions must include this license, modification notices, and use restrictions.

Section III: TRAIL-S (Source Code & Complementary Material)

Copyleft Requirement
Modified source code distributed must be released under TRAIL-S.

Linking Exception
Applications merely linking or importing may use any license.

Compatibility
Compatible with permissive licenses (MIT, Apache 2.0) provided TRAIL clauses remain.

Section IV: TRAIL-D (Datasets)

Use & Distribution
Datasets may be freely used, redistributed, modified.

Derivative Datasets
Released derivatives must include TRAIL-D with attribution.

Privacy & Legality
Users must ensure dataset usage complies with privacy and law.

Section V: Disclaimer & Liability
Licensed Work is provided “AS IS,” without warranty.
Licensors/contributors are not liable for damages.
Any additional warranties/obligations are solely your responsibility.

Attachment A
Use Restrictions
ou agree not to use the Model or its Derivatives in any of the following ways:

1. Legal
(a) In any way that violates any applicable national, federal, state, local or international law or regulation.

2. Harm and Discrimination
(a) For the purpose of exploiting, Harming or attempting to exploit or Harm minors in any way;
(b) To generate or disseminate false information with the purpose of Harming others;
(c) To generate or disseminate personal identifiable information that can be used to Harm an individual;
(d) To defame, disparage or otherwise harass others;
(e) For any use intended to or which has the effect of Harming individuals or groups based on online or offline social behavior or known or predicted personal or personality characteristics
(f) To exploit any of the vulnerabilities of a specific group of persons based on their age, social, physical or mental characteristics, in order to materially distort the behavior of a person belonging to that group in a manner that causes or is likely to cause that person or another person Harm
(g) For any use intended to or which has the effect of discriminating against individuals or groups based on legally protected characteristics or categories.

3. Transparency
(a) To generate or disseminate machine-generated information or content in any medium  without expressly and intelligibly disclaiming that it is machine-generated;
(b) To impersonate or attempt to impersonate human beings for purposes of deception;
(c) For fully automated decision making that adversely impacts an individual’s legal rights or otherwise creates or modifies a binding, enforceable obligation.

TRAIL – Taiwan Responsible AI License
Version 0.1, September 30, 2025

前言 / Preamble
TRAIL 結合 LGPL 的共享精神（修改必須開源、允許鏈接例外）與 RAIL 的責任限制（禁止違法或有害用途）。
本條款適用於三個部分：
TRAIL-M：模型與權重
TRAIL-S：程式碼與輔助材料
TRAIL-D：資料集

定義
(a) Model：包含架構、權重、參數（含 optimizer 狀態等）的機器學習模型。
(b) Complementary Material：與模型相關的程式碼、腳本、文件，用於定義、訓練、推論、評估。
(c) Dataset：用於訓練或評估模型的資料集。
(d) Derivative Work：對模型、程式碼或資料集進行修改、再訓練、蒸餾、轉換或其他衍生之成果。
(e) Linked Work：僅呼叫或載入模型／程式庫，未修改本身之應用程式。
(f) Distribution：向第三方提供模型、程式碼或資料集的方式（下載、API、遠端存取等）。
(g) Output：模型執行所產生的輸出。
(h) 「你」（或「你的」）：指依本授權行使權限，及／或以任何目的、於任何使用領域中使用本模型的個人或法人實體，包括在最終使用應用程式中使用模型的情境，例如：chatbot, translator, image generator。

第一節：智慧財產權授權 / Intellectual Property Rights
著作權授權
每位貢獻者授予你全球、免費、不可撤回的權利，使用、修改、散布 Licensed Work 與衍生版本。
專利授權
在法律允許範圍內，授予實施 Licensed Work 所需之專利使用權。若你對授權方提起專利訴訟，本授權即終止。

第二節：TRAIL-M（模型與權重）
修改必須開源
若你修改或建立衍生模型並加以分發，必須以 TRAIL-M 公開，並提供可存取之權重或程式碼。
允許連接例外
若僅透過 API、推論或載入模型使用，應用程式可任意授權，無需開源。
分發條件
分發時需附上本授權副本、修改標示、以及使用限制。

第三節：TRAIL-S（程式碼與輔助材料）
修改必須開源
若修改並再分發程式碼，必須以 TRAIL-S 公開。
允許連接例外
僅引用或鏈接程式庫之應用程式可任意授權，無需開源。
授權相容性
可與 MIT、Apache 2.0 等授權共存，但不得移除 TRAIL 條款。

第四節：TRAIL-D（資料集）
使用與分發
資料集可自由使用、再分發、修改。
衍生資料集
若公開衍生版本，必須附帶 TRAIL-D 並標示來源。
隱私與合法性
使用者須確保資料不侵犯隱私或違反法律。

第五節：免責與責任限制 / Disclaimer & Liability
Licensed Work 按「現況」提供，不附任何保證。
作者與貢獻者不對任何損害負責。
額外保固或義務僅由分發者自行承擔。

附件 A 使用限制
你同意不得以下列方式使用本模型或其衍生作品：
1. 法律 (Legal)
(a) 以任何違反適用的國家、聯邦、州、省、市或國際法律或法規的方式使用。
2. 傷害與歧視 (Harm and Discrimination)
(a) 以任何方式剝削、傷害或企圖剝削、傷害未成年人；
(b) 為傷害他人之目的而生成或散布虛假資訊；
(c) 生成或散布可用來傷害個人的個人識別資訊；
(d) 誹謗、貶低或以其他方式騷擾他人；
(e) 基於線上或線下的社交行為，或已知或預測的個人／人格特徵，從事意圖或實際上對個人或群體造成傷害的任何使用；
(f) 利用特定群體因年齡、社會、身體或心理特徵的弱勢，對該群體成員的行為進行重大扭曲，造成或可能造成該人或他人受到傷害；
(g) 任何意圖或實際上基於法律保護的特徵或類別，對個人或群體進行歧視的使用。
3. 透明性 (Transparency)
(a) 在任何媒介中生成或散布機器生成的資訊或內容，而未明確且清楚地聲明其為機器生成；
(b) 冒充或企圖冒充人類，以達成欺騙目的；
(c) 在完全自動化的決策過程中使用，若該決策對個人的法律權利造成不利影響，或創建／修改具有約束力、可執行的義務。

